org.conqat.lib.commons.collections

Class CollectionMap<K,V,C extends java.util.Collection<V>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.conqat.lib.commons.collections.CollectionMap<K,V,C>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - the key type.
    V - the value type (i.e. the values stored in the collections).
    C - the collection type, which is made explicit at the interface.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ListMap, SetMap

    public class CollectionMap<K,V,C extends java.util.Collection<V>>
extends java.lang.Object
    A collection map deals with a map of collections, i.e. each key can store multiple elements. Depending on the collection implementation chosen, this can also be interpreted as a multi map.

    If you deal with the basic case of Maps and Lists, use the ListMap, which is much easier to apply.
